00:44:08.740 --> 00:44:10.040
That's a good question.

00:44:10.040 --> 00:44:15.150
I know it was acquired by Arthur
Dunkelman [phonetic] on behalf

00:44:15.150 --> 00:44:20.560
of Jay Kislak for the
Kislak collection

00:44:20.560 --> 00:44:25.290
where it was originally was where
Arthur Dunkelman acquired it

00:44:25.290 --> 00:44:28.880
and under which conditions
I don't know.

00:44:37.510 --> 00:45:23.140
